                            <comment id="52603" author="recoco" created="Thu, 1 Apr 2010 12:52:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Anticipate this feature.&lt;br/&gt;
Now if I use @Valid with JSR-303 Constraints group , Spring cant binding failure messages to BindingResult. If only @Valid with Default group, Spring can binding failure messages to BindingResult. &lt;br/&gt;
So for the complex situation such as a create controller and a update controller which have different constraints group, it&apos;s very inconvenient.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
